#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.promote_types:2
msgid ""
"Returns the data type with the smallest size and smallest scalar kind to "
"which both ``type1`` and ``type2`` may be safely cast. The returned data "
"type is always considered \"canonical\", this mainly means that the promoted "
"dtype will always be in native byte order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
